Plug Hat is the American term for the British "top hat," a man's tall cylindrical hat with a narrow brim, made of silk plush. The wearing of these hats, also known as "stove pipe hats" was popularized by Abraham Lincoln during his presidency. Very early top hats were made of beaver felt.

